Saint Petersburg State University (SPbU) is a historic and prestigious public research university located in Saint Petersburg, Russia. Founded in 1724 by a decree from Peter the Great, it is among the oldest higher education institutions in the country, maintaining a strong focus on fundamental research in science and engineering. The university is organized into 24 distinct departments and institutes across two main campuses on Vasilievsky Island and in Peterhof. It serves a large academic community, boasting a student population of 32,400 (including 26,872 undergraduates and 5,566 postgraduates) and an administrative staff of 13,000.
