Victor Drits (Russian: Виктор Анатольевич Дриц, romanized: Viktor Anatolyevich Drits; November 25, 1932 – September 10, 2025) was a Soviet and Russian geologist, mineralogist, and crystallographer, professor, deputy director of the Geological Institute of the USSR Academy of Sciences / Russian Academy of Sciences (1988–1992). He was an expert in structural mineralogy and chemistry, with special interests in clay minerals.

Victor Drits graduated from Irkutsk State University in 1955. In 1961 obtained his Ph.D. degree in Solid State Physics and Crystallography from the Institute of Crystallography, USSR Academy of Sciences, Moscow, USSR.

Awards:
- 1996: Bailey Distinguished Member Award, Clay Minerals Society
- Doctor Honoris Causa of the Orléans University, France
- Honorary Member of the Mineralogical Society of Great Britain and Ireland

Monographs:
- Рентгеноструктурный анализ смешанослойных минералов (1976)
- Структурное исследование минералов методами микродифракции электронов и электронной микроскопии высокого разрешения (1981)
- Гипергенные окислы марганца (1989)
- Глинистые минералы: Смектиты, смешанослойные образования (1990)
- Глинистые минералы: слюды, хлориты (1991)
- Electron Diffraction and High-Resolution Electron Microscopy of Mineral Structures, Springer, 2012
- X-Ray Diffraction by Disordered Lamellar Structures: Theory and Applications to Microdivided Silicates and Carbons, Springer, 2012

Summary: 
Victor Drits (1932–2025) was a prominent Soviet and Russian geologist, mineralogist, and crystallographer who specialized in structural mineralogy, chemistry, and clay minerals. He served as a professor and deputy director of the Geological Institute of the USSR/Russian Academy of Sciences from 1988 to 1992. Drits earned his degree from Irkutsk State University in 1955 and a Ph.D. in Solid State Physics and Crystallography in 1961. Throughout his distinguished career, he received multiple awards, including the 1996 Bailey Distinguished Member Award and honorary affiliations in France and the UK, and he authored numerous monographs on mineral structures and clay minerals.
